        <abstract>
            <p>Can understand EH’s feelings on death of his wife.</p> 
<p>CD was impressed by manner in which species in South America are replaced by closely allied ones, by affinity of species inhabiting islands near S. America, and by relation of living Edentata and Rodentia to extinct species. When he read Malthus <hi rend="italic">On population</hi>, the idea of natural selection flashed on him.</p>  
<p>Agrees with EH’s remarks on Kölliker ["Darwin’sche Schöpfungstheorie", <hi rend="italic">Z. Wiss. Zool.</hi> 14 (1864): 174–86].</p>  
<p>Asks EH to thank Carl Gegenbaur [for <hi rend="italic">Vergleichende Anatomie der Wirbelthiere</hi> (1864)].</p> 
        </abstract>
